Definition: a political system governed by a few people
Example: one of his cardinal convictions was that Britain was not run as a democracy but as an oligarchy; the big cities were notoriously in the hands of the oligarchy of local businessmen
Synonyms: adj, pert, oligarchic, oligarchical, political_system, a, political, system, governed, by, few, people, one, of, his, cardinal, convictions, was, that, Britain, not, run, as, democracy, but, an, the, big, cities, were, notoriously, in, hands, local, businessmen
Category: noun.group
